$ VBA: vba6 and vba7 predefined compiler directive constants

The → development/languages/VBA/compiler-directives/const#vba-predefined-compiler-constants[predefined compiler constants] `vba6` and `vba7` allow to determine if a VBA environment is compatible to the VBA specification 6 or 7.

If `vba7` is true, it implies that `vba6` is also true.

gh|about-VBA|/compiler-directives/vbaX/compiler-versions.bas||

The `vba7` constant is especially useful for the → development/languages/VBA/language/32-vs-64-bit#vba_32_64_ptrSafe[conditionally declaring functions with `ptrSafe`].

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/compiler-directives/conditional-compilation[Conditional compilation in VBA]
